infos.info: Hickerson reports the broadcast history dates during the period 7/29/35 - 6/28/54 as: ';7/29/35 -7/5/37; 9/13/37 -7/4/38; 9/12/38 -7/10/39; 9/11/39 -7/8/40; 9/9/40 -717/41; 9/8/41-7/20/42; 9/14/42 -7/12/43; 9/13/43 -7/3/44; 9/4/44-6/25/45; 8/27/45 -6/24/46; 8/26/46-6/23/47; 8/25/47 -6/28/48; 8/30/48 - 6/27/49; 8/29/49 - 6/26/50; 8/28/50 - 6/25/51; 8/27/51- 5/26/52; 9/8/52 - 6/28/54 ... from New York until 5/25/36; from Hollywood starting with 6/1/36; 6/1/53 - 8/31/53 called Summer Theater.'; - Dunning shows Broadcast history: Oct.14, 1934- June 30, 1935 on the Blue Network. - John Anthony, fictionalized as ' Douglass Garrick' - Sound effects: Max Uhlig, David Light, Walter Pierson, Charlie Forsyth. - Orchestra: Robert Armbruster. 1936 Louis Silvers, until ca. 1951 - Also as writer: George Wells.
